          }
        },
        "copy": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Mouse meets Fox, Owl and Snake one by one. Each animal thinks Mouse might make a meal, and each one is scared away by Mouse’s invented Gruffalo. When the real Gruffalo appears, the pattern flips: Mouse uses the other animals’ fear to outwit the monster too.</p><p>This repeated structure is one reason the book is so easy for children to remember and retell.</p>"
